==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonophant
<hw>Ton"o*phant</hw> <pr>(t⟦omac⟧n"⟦osl⟧*f⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>to`nos</grk> a tone + <grk>fai`nein</grk> to show.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics.)</fld> <def>A modification of the kaleidophon, for
showing composition of acoustic vibrations. It consists of two thin
slips of steel welded together, their length being adjustable by a screw
socket.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tonous</ent>⟦br⟧
